\par \pard\plain \widctlpar \f5\fs20\lang2057 This dialog enables you to select how your references are sorted.
\par 
\par {\i Refs} will first makes comparisons between references on the basis of the first field.  If these are the same it will then try the second field and so on.
\par 
\par For each comparison you can choose which field to sort on, and whether you want ascending or descending order.  The default is to sort Author (Ascending), Date (Ascending), Title (Ascending).
\par 
\par As with the {\strike list options dialog box}{\v ListOpt}, these options are saved on a per-window basis, and the most recently given options are saved to the INI file and used to sort new files, and files being loaded.
\par 
