\par {\b\cf9 \tab Example 1 - Plain Times New Roman}{\b 
\par }
\par Based upon the simple RTF reference format supplied with {\i Refs}, we can add a font table with just Time New Roman and set the standard font to Times New Roman at 14 points. As thi
s is a very common font we omit the font family, character set and pitch for simplicity. Other formatting included here is the journal or book title in italics and the volume number in bold. The double paragraph marks at the end create a blank line betwee
n references. The final {\f11 \\n\\n} inserts a blank line between the references in the formatted bibliography window.
\par 
\par {\f11 RTF2=[\{\\\\rtf1\\ansi \{\\\\fonttbl\{\\\\f0 Times New Roman;\}\}\\\\f0\\\\fs28 ][\}]<A@ ><D(@)>, <T"@"<B in <E@ (ed.), >>><J, \{\\\\i @\}<V, vol. \{\\\\b @\}><N, no. @>><B\{\\\\i @\}<I, @><C, @>><T<P, pp. @>>\{\\\\par\}\{\\\\par\}\\n\\n
\par }
